cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.AI 

This paper deals with the simulation of diffusion processes through social networks and geographic locations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also uses probabilistic models and survival analysis, which are common in the sub-categories cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The study of network structures and individual transmissions also falls under the sub-category cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks). Finally, the use of machine learning techniques to model the diffusion process suggests a possible fit with the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
